tourBios.personal: Has a twin brother who represented Australia in cricket...Biggest thrill in golf was teeing it up on at the 2012 Open Championship...Would love to hear Drake's "Headlines" on the first tee before his round...Not many people know he stopped playing cricket because he could longer compete with his brother...List Bora Bora as his dream destination. Would love to be featured in Time one day because it would mean he "has made a difference in the world."...Would love to trade places with Lewis Hamilton and drive a Formula-1 car...Picked golf over other sports because he liked that "all of the responsibility falls on you."...If he weren't playing golf he would work in snowboard shop at a ski resort in Colorado...Earliest golf memory was playing with plastic golf clubs in the backyard with his brother when they wereage 7...Enjoys spending time with family when not playing golf...Twitter account is @nickcullengolf.
tourBios.priorYearSeason:
2015: Competed at the World Golf Championships-HSBC Champions on the PGA TOUR. Carded 74-71-70-73 for a T58...Played in three European Tour events and made the cut in each of them. His best finish was a T56 at the Volvo China Masters.

2014: Won the Australian Masters by one stroke over James Nitties, Adam Scott and Josh Younger

2013: Won the Queensland Open

2012: Won the Enjoy Jakarta Indonesia Open on the OneAsia Tour.
